# Digital Attendance System for Hour-Based Lectures

**Course:** EEE227 - Introduction to C++ Programming  
**Programme:** HND Electrical Engineering, Level 200  
**Developer:** Franklin Sampson  
**Platform:** Windows (Offline, Console-based)

---

## Overview

A console-based digital attendance management system built in C++.
It replaces paper-based attendance with a secure, file-backed system
that supports multiple lecture sessions, student management, and
CSV export for reporting.

---

## How to Compile and Run

**Requirements:** A C++ compiler (g++ recommended via MinGW on Windows)
```bash
g++ -o attendance main.cpp
attendance.exe
```

Or open the project folder in VS Code and use the built-in Run button.

---

## First Run

On first launch the system will ask you to create an admin account.
Choose a username and password — these are stored in `admin.txt`.
You will need these credentials every time you start the program.

---

## Main Menu Options

| Option | Feature |
|--------|---------|
| 1 | Student Management |
| 2 | Session Management |
| 3 | Mark / Update Attendance |
| 4 | Reports and Export |
| 5 | Admin Tools |
